hopobject.body: Just over two years satibo capsule srbija Former San Diego Mayor Bob Filner, left, stands with counsel in court and takes an oath before he pleads guilty on state charges of felony false imprisonment Tuesday, Oct. 15, 2013 in San Diego. Filner pleaded guilty to one criminal count of false imprisonment by violence, fraud, menace and deceit and two misdemeanor counts of battery. The charges involve three unnamed women victims. Filner, 71, resigned in late August, succumbing to intense pressure after at least 17 women brought lurid sexual harassment allegations. (AP Photo/UT-San Diego, John Gibbins, Pool)
